        "procedure_content": "1. Select your bet using in-game points\n2. Two cards are dealt to you and one card to the dealer\n3. Choose HIT to draw a card, or STAND to keep your hand\n4. Dealer plays automatically\n5. Win/Lose/Push is shown, then proceed to the next round",
        "description_title_1": "Basic Rules",
        "description_content_1": "Aim to get as close to 21 as possible.\nIf your total exceeds 21, you lose immediately (Bust).\nIf you are closer to 21 than the dealer, you win.\n\n- Blackjack: 21 with the first two cards (A + 10-value card)\n- Bust: Total is 22 or more\n- Push: Tie (same total)",
        "description_title_2": "Card Values",
        "description_content_2": "- Number cards (2-10): Face value\n- Face cards (J, Q, K): 10\n- Ace (A): 11 or 1 (auto-adjusted depending on the situation)\n\nTip: Aces are flexible, so keeping an Ace can help avoid busting.",
        "description_title_3": "Dealer Rules / Tips",
        "description_content_3": "Dealer rules:\n- Dealer must draw until reaching 17 or more\n- Dealer must stand on 17 or more\n\nStrategy tips:\n- If your total is 17 or higher, STAND is often safer\n- If your total is 11 or lower, HIT is usually safe (no immediate bust)\n- If you have an Ace counted as 11, you can take more risks because it can become 1 automatically\n\nIf you run out of points, you can reset them to 100 from Settings.",
        "supported_languages_title": "Supported Languages",
        "supported_languages_content": "English\nJapanese\nSimplified Chinese\n* Please note that some gameplay-related terms may be displayed in English only.",
